00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:04.019
Welcome my friend to today's
lecture on general Knowledge.

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:07.680
Ever felt like your
brain needed a power up.

00:00:08.070 --> 00:00:08.280
This is it.

00:00:10.245 --> 00:00:16.515
Concept explanation, general knowledge,
or GK as we fondly call it in the

00:00:16.515 --> 00:00:21.884
context of your exam, is basically
a giant test of are you living on

00:00:21.884 --> 00:00:24.255
this planet or did you just arrive?

00:00:24.795 --> 00:00:29.564
It refers to a broad understanding
of various facts and information

00:00:29.715 --> 00:00:31.305
across different domains.

00:00:31.775 --> 00:00:35.585
It covers everything from what's
happening in the world right now,

00:00:35.735 --> 00:00:40.805
which we call current events to static
information about history, geography,

00:00:40.985 --> 00:00:46.565
Indian polity, economy, science, and
of course specific knowledge related

00:00:46.565 --> 00:00:48.754
to the banking and financial sector.

00:00:49.190 --> 00:00:54.110
The goal is single to see how aware
you are of the world around you.

00:00:54.589 --> 00:00:59.629
It's not about becoming a PhD in
every subject, but having a general

00:00:59.629 --> 00:01:01.519
grasp of important information.

00:01:02.030 --> 00:01:05.539
Think of it as knowing a little
bit about a lot of things.

00:01:06.795 --> 00:01:08.145
Real world relevance.

00:01:08.655 --> 00:01:11.085
And why is this so important you ask?

00:01:11.445 --> 00:01:16.035
Well, general knowledge is incredibly
crucial for banking professionals

00:01:16.185 --> 00:01:20.955
because it provides the foundation for
understanding the wider world where

00:01:21.015 --> 00:01:23.235
all financial decisions are made.

00:01:23.745 --> 00:01:28.215
It helps in understanding economic
policies and tricky market trends.

00:01:28.645 --> 00:01:34.075
This awareness enables informed decision
making in complex financial scenarios,

00:01:34.225 --> 00:01:36.115
which is a big part of the job.

00:01:36.565 --> 00:01:41.185
It also aids in effective communication
with a diverse range of clients.

00:01:41.634 --> 00:01:45.925
Having this knowledge provides a broader
context for financial discussions,

00:01:46.104 --> 00:01:50.304
building your credibility and trust
with both clients and colleagues.

00:01:50.664 --> 00:01:55.315
You'll sound like you know what you're
talking about because you actually will.

00:01:56.339 --> 00:01:58.199
Breakdown of question types.

