About 40% of the weightage is on current
affairs, which includes national and

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:16.620
international news awards, sports
summits, and government schemes.

00:02:17.010 --> 00:02:21.450
Another 30% is dedicated to
banking and financial awareness,

00:02:21.570 --> 00:02:22.890
covering banking terms.

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:27.270
RBI functions, financial
institutions and economic concepts.

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:31.620
This is the core, my friend,
static General Knowledge makes up

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:37.200
about 20%, which includes history,
geography, Indian polity, science

00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:39.450
books, authors, and important days.

00:02:40.055 --> 00:02:44.645
Finally, a miscellaneous 10% is
sprinkled in covering basics of

00:02:44.645 --> 00:02:46.325
computer knowledge and general science.

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:49.380
Formulas and tricks.

00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:55.530
Now, for the magical part formulas, I have
to break it to you for general knowledge.

00:02:55.590 --> 00:02:58.019
There are no formulas like in mathematics.

00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:02.250
Instead, we focus on memory
aids and strategic approaches.

00:03:03.090 --> 00:03:07.829
You can create acronyms and mnemonics,
which are short, memorable phrases

00:03:07.950 --> 00:03:10.560
like for the colors of the rainbow.

00:03:11.010 --> 00:03:16.019
Another trick is association where you
link new information with something you

00:03:16.019 --> 00:03:18.660
already know, creating a stronger memory.

00:03:19.055 --> 00:03:21.424
Flashcards are a classic for a reason.

00:03:21.605 --> 00:03:25.204
They are great for quick recall of
facts through spaced repetition.

00:03:25.565 --> 00:03:31.115
You can also try mind maps to visually
organize information and please use

00:03:31.115 --> 00:03:36.095
categorization group similar facts
together like all national parks or

00:03:36.095 --> 00:03:39.935
all recent government appointments
to make them easier to remember.

00:03:40.295 --> 00:03:45.245
Finally, the golden rule is repetition
with spacing, review information

00:03:45.245 --> 00:03:48.425
at increasing intervals to really
lock it into your long-term memory.

00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:51.704
Methods of solving.

00:03:52.424 --> 00:03:52.994
All right.

00:03:53.174 --> 00:03:57.494
How do you actually solve these questions
in the exam hall without panicking?

00:03:58.065 --> 00:04:01.845
The main game here is recall
and logical elimination.

00:04:02.355 --> 00:04:05.415
First, please read the question carefully.

00:04:05.894 --> 00:04:09.075
Look for sneaky keywords,
like not correct or incorrect.

00:04:10.760 --> 00:04:14.894
If you know the answer directly,
brilliant, mark it and move on.

00:04:15.364 --> 00:04:19.415
If not, it's time for the
superstar method elimination.

00:04:19.865 --> 00:04:24.395
Go through the options one by one
and eliminate the ones you are sure

00:04:24.425 --> 00:04:26.945
are wrong or completely irrelevant.

00:04:27.425 --> 00:04:31.025
This dramatically increases your
chances of getting it right.

00:04:31.534 --> 00:04:37.235
Sometimes the question itself or the other
options can give you contextual clues.

00:04:37.505 --> 00:04:42.950
So be a bit of a detective and as a
last resort, if you've narrowed it down.

00:04:43.290 --> 00:04:47.700
Make an educated guess, but
please avoid blind guessing

00:04:47.730 --> 00:04:49.320
if there's negative marking.

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:50.415
That's a trap.

00:04:51.345 --> 00:04:55.515
Shortcuts and smart techniques
want some smart techniques.

00:04:55.695 --> 00:04:59.295
The best one is making daily
news consumption a habit.

00:04:59.835 --> 00:05:04.185
Pick a reputable newspaper or a
reliable news app and make it your

00:05:04.185 --> 00:05:09.975
daily companion, focusing on national,
international economic and banking news.

00:05:10.409 --> 00:05:14.039
To revise, refer to monthly
current affairs, compilations

00:05:14.070 --> 00:05:15.450
from trusted sources.

00:05:15.930 --> 00:05:20.700
Pay extra special attention to
banking specifics like RBI policies,

00:05:20.849 --> 00:05:25.049
banking terminology, recent
mergers and financial schemes.

00:05:25.450 --> 00:05:30.640
It's also very smart to analyze previous
year papers to understand frequently

00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:32.680
asked topics and question patterns.

00:05:33.190 --> 00:05:37.660
Keep quick revision notes for last
minute review of important facts and

00:05:37.660 --> 00:05:40.600
dates and for a bit of passive learning.

00:05:40.780 --> 00:05:44.425
Listen to audio podcasts or
watch video summaries of current

00:05:44.545 --> 00:05:46.185
events during your commute.

00:05:46.685 --> 00:05:50.265
It all adds up common
mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:51.195 --> 00:05:53.625
Now let's talk about the common pitfalls.

00:05:53.625 --> 00:06:00.224
To avoid a huge mistake is relying solely
on static GK like history and geography,

00:06:00.465 --> 00:06:05.174
while ignoring current affairs, which
often forms the largest part of the paper.

00:06:05.745 --> 00:06:08.924
Another one is underestimating
banking awareness.

00:06:09.344 --> 00:06:14.294
These financial terms are critical for
a banking exam, so do not skip them.

00:06:14.735 --> 00:06:18.995
